OL,7,FYet two years on today, while Sudan's
OL,8,Fcapital may no longer be burning as it
OL,9,Fonce did, it is an empty shell,
OL,10,Fhollowed out, destroyed and vacant of
OL,11,Fthe vibrant communities that made up
OL,12,Fwhat it once was. And crucially,
OL,13,FSudan's agony has got worse.
OL,15,FMinisters and representatives from 20
OL,16,Fcountries gathered in London today for
OL,17,Fthe Sudan Conference, hosted by
OL,18,FForeign Secretary David Lammy, to
OL,19,Fdiscuss restarting stalled peace talks
OL,20,Fand find "a pathway to peace".
